      "SummaryText": "he threshold quantity of 10,000 pounds are Isobutylene, Butene, Isobutane, Propane, Propylene, and Butane.  Gas Innovations also handles Hydrogen Chloride in exceedance of its threshold quantity of 5,000 pounds.  These gases are distributed to clients in bulk or cylinders.  These regulated substances are stored at the site in bulk process storage tanks.  These tanks are filled between 85% and 88% of their capacity.  The expected quantities stored and used at the site of these regulated substances vary from 17,000 pounds to 62,000 pounds.  \n\n \nAccidental Release Prevention Program\n\nGas Innovations has implemented an emergency response program that includes incident prevention and investigation.  The bulk storage tanks are equipped with release prevention devices that include emergency shut-off, manual valves, purge flow valves, relief valves, high pressure regulators and back check valves.  The equipment is included in a prevention maintenance program as recommended by the equipment manufacturers.\n\nGas Innovations is subject to the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) Process Safety Management (PSM) rules.  The site has performed process hazards review to the regulated processes under the Risk Management Program (RMP), which includes the flammable gases and the hydrogen chloride storage and handling processes.\n\nFive Year Accident History\n\nIn the past five years Gas Innovations has had no accidental releases of the regulated substances that can cause death, injury, property or environmental damage, evacuations, or sheltering in place.\n\nEmergency Response Program\n\nThe facility has an Emergency Response (ER) program which has been coordinated with the community.  The facility's ER program includes specific actions to be taken in response to accidental releases of the regulated substances.  The facility's ER program includes procedures for informing the public and local agencies responding to accidental releases at the site.  The facility's ER program inc"
